   ISO 9001


     On September 17, 1999, all of NASA Centers, NASA Headquarters, the Jet
     Propulsion Laboratory and all of NASAÂ’s Government Operated Facilities
     achieved ISO 9001 registration. With this achievement, NASA became the
     first Government Agency in the World (Federal or State) to have
     multiple sites under an ISO 9001 registration.

     For general information about ISO go to http://www.iso.ch/.

     This web site serves as a resource tool for employees, contractors, and
     NASA management at all levels. It contains information and links
     related to NASA's Quality Management Systems.


